Class RegionValues

  • java.lang.Object
    • param.RegionValues
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<java.util.Map.Entry<Region,StateValues>>

    public final class RegionValues
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<java.util.Map.Entry<Region,StateValues>>
    Assigns to the different regions different values over model states. For each region for which values have been decided, an object of this class contains a value for each state.
    Author:
    Ernst Moritz Hahn (University of Oxford)

        For each region, print part of vector to a log/file.
        Parameters:
        log - The log
        mode - the mode
        filter - A BitSet specifying which states to print for (null if all).
        printSparse - Print non-zero/non-false elements only?
        printStates - Print states (variable values) for each element?
        printIndices - Print state indices for each element?
